Uses of Package
processingwrapper

  • Classes in processingwrapper used by processingwrapper 
    Class Description
    Canvas
    A canvas is an entity that contains elements to be drawn on the screen.
    Circle
    A circle that can be drawn in the screen.
    Drawable
    Instances of this class are packages of a drawable thing (like a shape or an image or a canvas) and settings for how to draw them (like ImageSettings or ShapeSettings).
    Ellipse
    An ellipse that can be drawn in the screen.
    Image
    An image loaded from a file.
    ImageSettings
    The ImageSettings class is used to define the aesthetic properties of an Image.
    Position
    The Position class is used to specify the position where an object is drawn on a canvas.
    Position.DrawMode
    The Position.DrawMode class is used to specify the drawing mode of objects.
    ProcessingApp
    ProcessingApp is the interface implemented by client applications.
    Rectangle
    A rectangle that can be drawn in the screen.
    Shape
    If a class implements this class, then instances of that class can be combined with ShapeSettings to be drawn on the canvas as an argument to Canvas.draw(processingwrapper.Drawable, processingwrapper.Position).
    ShapeSettings
    The ShapeSettings class is used to define the aesthetic properties of the Rectangle, Ellipse, and Circle shapes.
